  <details><summary><span style="display: block; font-size: 24px;">Privacy policy</span></summary>
    <h1 class="details">At EMPYREAN inc., we strive to protect your privacy.<br>You get to choose what data gets sent to us.</h1>
    <ul class="details">
      <li>Turn off analytic data sharing.</li>
      <p class="details">We analyze your behavior and the games you play to further improve our service. We also analyze your system to get
        a better picture of the type of hardware our users use. We collect information about the duration and the games that you play to be
        added into our databases. They provide us valuable information about what games are popular and what are not. They will also be published
        on our leaderboards. You have the option to opt-out of these features.
      </p>
      <li>Turn off personalized ad settings.</li>
      <p class="details">Based off the genre of games you play and your interactions with other people, we generate personalized interest that
        we guess you might like to further improve your ad experience. Please note that by turning this feature off, you will still receive ads 
        wherever applicable and the same frequency had you turned it on. However, the ads may not be as accurate and may not reflect your personal
        interests. Nevertheless, we provide you the option to opt-out of these features.
      </p>
      <li>Turn off performance tracking</li>
      <p class="details">We also collect information about your system's performance like for example, latency, client FPS, and RAM usage.
        These information will be used to revise our system requirements from time-to-time to better reflect real world conditions and to 
        accomodate a wider range of users by providing guidelines for multiple platforms. For example, for Nvidia and AMD GPUs. We assure you
        that these trackers will take up no more than 25MB of RAM and 5% of CPU usage, they will only have a negligeble impact on network 
        performance (around 20Kbps). However, if maximum performance or privacy is your priority, you can opt-out of these trackers.
      </p></ul>
      <h2 class="details">Guidelines on opting out</h2>
      <p class="details">While being on your client's home page, navigate to settings, click the Privacy tab on the left side, disable the
        respective checkboxes. After finishing your features, click Save on the bottom right corner to refresh your changes.
    </p><br></details><br>
